
1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Subhas Chandra Bose — the fearless freedom fighter with a vision of an independent India.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
He left the Congress over ideological differences and formed the Indian National Army.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
"Give me blood, and I shall give you freedom" — his call electrified the youth.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,000
With Japanese support, Bose fought British forces in Burma and Imphal.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Though he vanished mysteriously in 1945, Bose’s legacy lives on as Netaji — the eternal patriot.
